1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,261
A couple days ago, we got the release of the new Minecraft 26.1 drop,

2
00:00:04,260 --> 00:00:06,655
otherwise known as the Tiny Takeover.

3
00:00:06,655 --> 00:00:07,815
Or as I like to call it,

4
00:00:07,820 --> 00:00:10,068
the Wholesome Reddit Chungus Update!

5
00:00:10,070 --> 00:00:10,930
Approved!

6
00:00:10,930 --> 00:00:13,845
Yeah, I'm sorry to start this video out by immediately complaining,

7
00:00:13,850 --> 00:00:17,059
but this is by far the weakest game drop we've gotten so far.

8
00:00:17,059 --> 00:00:18,608
The main focus for this update

9
00:00:18,608 --> 00:00:21,700
was changing the models and textures for all of the game's baby mobs.

10
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:22,892
Besides that though,

11
00:00:22,892 --> 00:00:26,125
there was practically nothing of value added to this update.

12
00:00:26,125 --> 00:00:27,130
But that's okay!

13
00:00:27,130 --> 00:00:29,032
Look at the heckin' doggos!

14
00:00:29,619 --> 00:00:33,160
I just don't interact with baby mobs pretty much at all,

15
00:00:33,160 --> 00:00:35,709
and while I know every drop isn't going to appeal to me,

16
00:00:35,709 --> 00:00:38,405
I feel like there still could have been a little bit more done here.

17
00:00:38,405 --> 00:00:40,715
Spring to Life, for example, isn't my favorite drop,

18
00:00:40,715 --> 00:00:43,365
but at least it gave us a few pretty helpful building blocks.

19
00:00:43,370 --> 00:00:44,794
Baby mobs, in comparison,

20
00:00:44,790 --> 00:00:47,213
are not a big aspect of the game at all.

21
00:00:47,210 --> 00:00:50,238
At most, I pretty much just see them when I'm breeding animals.

22
00:00:50,238 --> 00:00:53,655
I genuinely don't see this update changing how I play the game very much,

23
00:00:53,655 --> 00:00:56,285
which is not the case for every other drop they've done.

24
00:00:56,290 --> 00:00:58,958
Now that's not to say that the new baby mobs are ugly,

25
00:00:58,960 --> 00:01:00,001
well at least not all of them,

26
00:01:00,353 --> 00:01:04,010
I just don't think this update is all that interesting for the overall game.

27
00:01:04,010 --> 00:01:05,325
But there were a few,

28
00:01:05,325 --> 00:01:06,725
emphasis on the few,

29
00:01:06,730 --> 00:01:08,386
features outside of just the babies,

30
00:01:08,390 --> 00:01:12,626
so today, I'm going to be ranking every feature added in the 26.1 drop.

31
00:01:13,545 --> 00:01:15,395
Okay, before half of you get confused,

32
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:18,392
YouTube lets creators test multiple titles and thumbnails at the same time

33
00:01:18,390 --> 00:01:19,683
to see which does the best.

34
00:01:19,683 --> 00:01:22,940
So half of you will get my standard 26.1 drop thumbnail,

35
00:01:22,940 --> 00:01:25,092
whereas the other half will get the thumbnail about

36
00:01:25,092 --> 00:01:27,135
ranking every baby mob in Minecraft.

37
00:01:27,135 --> 00:01:30,395
There wasn't enough content to justify making this two separate videos,

38
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:31,959
so here's how this is going to work.

39
00:01:31,959 --> 00:01:35,192
I'll be going down the 26.1 feature ranking list as normal,

40
00:01:35,192 --> 00:01:37,400
and when we reach the entry containing the baby mobs,

41
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:40,684
we'll break off into the baby ranking before returning to the main video.

42
00:01:40,684 --> 00:01:43,360
If you literally only care about ranking babies,

43
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:46,255
I'll include a chapter for that section so you can skip right to it.

44
00:01:46,255 --> 00:01:49,104
Just know that we will be making fun of you for being a Redditor,

45
00:01:49,100 --> 00:01:51,200
and you'll be missing out on some good content.

46
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:54,815
You'll never find out about this update's shocking polar bear change!

47
00:01:54,815 --> 00:01:56,958
Anyway, as always, I'll be ranking these features

48
00:01:56,958 --> 00:01:59,242
based on how much I like them for Java survival mode.

49
00:01:59,242 --> 00:02:01,208
That means features that are creative mode exclusive

50
00:02:01,208 --> 00:02:02,821
won't be included in this list.

51
00:02:02,820 --> 00:02:04,753
So with that said, if you enjoyed this video,

52
00:02:04,750 --> 00:02:06,772
please make sure to leave a like, subscribe to the channel,

53
00:02:06,772 --> 00:02:07,900
and let's jump right in.

54
00:02:09,640 --> 00:02:13,090
You know, on top of the additions in this update being lackluster,

55
00:02:13,085 --> 00:02:15,525
this is our first drop in a while to have a change

56
00:02:15,525 --> 00:02:18,085
that I think is honestly negative for the game.

57
00:02:18,085 --> 00:02:20,465
In fact, it's actually got several.

58
00:02:20,470 --> 00:02:22,944
Really not helping my opinion on this update.

59
00:02:22,944 --> 00:02:24,985
Oh but look at the cute baby Strider!

60
00:02:24,985 --> 00:02:25,808
Kicking us off,

61
00:02:25,808 --> 00:02:29,305
we actually have a feature that was straight up removed from the game.

62
00:02:29,310 --> 00:02:30,000
Twelve.

63
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:32,000
They killed the baby camel husk.

64
00:02:33,358 --> 00:02:35,192
Yeah, I guess they just didn't want to bother

65
00:02:35,192 --> 00:02:36,970
making a new baby variant for this guy,

66
00:02:36,970 --> 00:02:40,540
so they completely removed the ability to have baby camel husks at all.

67
00:02:40,540 --> 00:02:41,940
If you had one in your world,

68
00:02:41,940 --> 00:02:45,123
they would just automatically be turned into an adult after the update.

69
00:02:45,123 --> 00:02:45,945
Now granted,

70
00:02:45,945 --> 00:02:49,110
I don't think you can actually get baby camel husks in survival,

71
00:02:49,110 --> 00:02:50,407
but it's still pretty lame to just

72
00:02:50,410 --> 00:02:52,928
remove the ability to spawn in the sky with commands.

73
00:02:53,158 --> 00:02:55,410
Wait, I said this video was survival mode only.

74
00:02:55,410 --> 00:02:55,955
Uh...

75
00:02:55,955 --> 00:02:56,710
Wait guys look!

76
00:02:56,710 --> 00:02:58,999
It's baby spooky camel drop!

77
00:03:02,997 --> 00:03:04,497
He's gone now.

78
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:08,075
Baby spooky camel drop is lost media.

79
00:03:08,075 --> 00:03:10,805
Now obviously this isn't like a devastating removal,

80
00:03:10,810 --> 00:03:13,292
I doubt 99% of the playerbase will care,

81
00:03:13,292 --> 00:03:15,342
but removing a feature for no real reason

82
00:03:15,342 --> 00:03:17,385
kind of has to be last place by default.

83
00:03:17,385 --> 00:03:18,015
Eleven.

84
00:03:18,015 --> 00:03:20,115
Wandering trader name tag change.

85
00:03:20,115 --> 00:03:22,355
Spoilers for a future entry.

86
00:03:22,355 --> 00:03:24,992
The name tag finally got a crafting recipe in this update

87
00:03:24,992 --> 00:03:27,225
requiring a piece of paper and a nugget.

88
00:03:27,230 --> 00:03:29,500
That is extraordinarily cheap,

89
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:32,558
especially considering how rare name tags were before this update.

90
00:03:32,558 --> 00:03:34,700
I mean they weren't like a shiny pokemon or something,

91
00:03:34,700 --> 00:03:36,575
but you needed to either find them in structures

92
00:03:36,575 --> 00:03:38,625
or get them from villager trading and fishing.

93
00:03:38,630 --> 00:03:41,317
Name tags used to be the final trade unlocked,

94
00:03:41,317 --> 00:03:44,135
and they were pretty expensive costing 20 emeralds each.

95
00:03:44,135 --> 00:03:45,920
With how cheap they are to craft now,

96
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:47,916
that trade is a complete scam,

97
00:03:47,916 --> 00:03:49,550
so they replaced it with something else.

98
00:03:49,550 --> 00:03:51,430
We'll talk about that trade in a little bit,

99
00:03:51,430 --> 00:03:54,792
but so far that tweak makes sense to go with the new crafting recipe.

100
00:03:54,792 --> 00:03:57,855
So why did they give the wandering trader a name tag trade?

101
00:03:57,855 --> 00:04:00,005
Yeah, this addition makes no sense to me.

102
00:04:00,010 --> 00:04:01,652
Now whenever a wandering trader spawns,

103
00:04:01,652 --> 00:04:04,030
it has a chance to trade a name tag for one emerald.

104
00:04:04,030 --> 00:04:06,125
Why would you literally ever do that

105
00:04:06,125 --> 00:04:08,212
with how cheap the crafting recipe is?

106
00:04:08,212 --> 00:04:09,960
Since this is a wandering trader too,

107
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:13,170
there's no way to get this trade reliably even if you do want it.

108
00:04:13,170 --> 00:04:16,011
In my opinion, this trade is completely worthless,

109
00:04:16,011 --> 00:04:19,380
which is bad because the wandering trader has a very limited trade pool.

110
00:04:19,380 --> 00:04:23,250
Each one will only spawn with nine completely random trades,

111
00:04:23,250 --> 00:04:25,175
so all this name tag trade does

112
00:04:25,175 --> 00:04:27,736
is make the actual useful trade slightly rarer

113
00:04:27,736 --> 00:04:30,076
since now it's one of the potential trade options.

114
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:33,726
I mean why would you ever want to do this trade over the sugar cane trade

115
00:04:33,730 --> 00:04:35,740
which are both competing for the same slot?

116
00:04:35,740 --> 00:04:38,999
If you say it saves you from needing to get any ores for nuggets,

117
00:04:38,999 --> 00:04:40,820
good luck using this without an anvil.

118
00:04:40,820 --> 00:04:43,020
Even in game modes like skyblock or superflat,

119
00:04:43,020 --> 00:04:45,082
where resources are super limited,

120
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:47,537
this trade is next to useless with the new recipe.

121
00:04:47,537 --> 00:04:49,875
So in my opinion, this is a negative addition

122
00:04:49,880 --> 00:04:52,606
that just makes the wandering trader less likely to be useful.

123
00:04:52,606 --> 00:04:54,530
Also I didn't realize this before getting footage,

124
00:04:54,530 --> 00:04:57,275
but the wandering trader can also now trade golden dandelions.

125
00:04:57,280 --> 00:05:00,608
And I only found that out because it took me forever to get the name tag trade.

126
00:05:04,810 --> 00:05:05,280
Ten.

127
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:07,615
Adult black dot horse texture change.

128
00:05:07,615 --> 00:05:09,490
In order to match with its baby variant,

129
00:05:09,490 --> 00:05:12,222
the adult black dot horse type also got a new texture.

130
00:05:14,636 --> 00:05:16,660
I think it's way uglier than the original.

131
00:05:16,655 --> 00:05:19,159
The black dots are integrated far less smoothly

132
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:22,258
and just feel like they were randomly thrown up on the horse's texture.

133
00:05:22,258 --> 00:05:26,310
I don't understand why they didn't just change the baby to match the original adult horse,

134
00:05:26,310 --> 00:05:28,425
because now both of them just look ugly.

135
00:05:28,430 --> 00:05:29,018
Nine.

136
00:05:29,020 --> 00:05:32,192
Baby polar bears no longer attack foxes.

137
00:05:32,192 --> 00:05:35,020
Bet you guys are so happy you didn't skip to the baby ranking.

138
00:05:35,020 --> 00:05:37,045
I didn't know they did this in the first place,

139
00:05:37,050 --> 00:05:39,075
but I guess it's tragic that we can no longer watch

140
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:40,825
BABY FIGHTS!

141
00:05:40,825 --> 00:05:41,240
Eight.

142
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:42,510
New animal noises.

143
00:05:42,510 --> 00:05:44,392
Okay, we are finally starting to get into

144
00:05:44,392 --> 00:05:46,146
the additions that are more positive.

145
00:05:46,146 --> 00:05:48,070
Several mobs got new sound variants,

146
00:05:48,065 --> 00:05:50,880
those being the cat, pig, chicken, and cow.

147
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:53,875
If you remember the wolf noises that got added a couple updates ago,

148
00:05:53,875 --> 00:05:55,600
this works in a very similar way.

149
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:57,145
The classic sounds still exist,

150
00:05:57,150 --> 00:05:59,258
but each of these animals also have a chance to spawn

151
00:05:59,258 --> 00:06:00,821
with a different set of noises.

152
00:06:00,820 --> 00:06:03,393
These noises are also independent from their biome variant,

153
00:06:03,393 --> 00:06:03,980
so there are now

154
00:06:03,980 --> 00:06:07,000
multiple combinations of sounds and textures for each of these mobs.

155
00:06:06,995 --> 00:06:09,500
This is far less expansive compared to the wolves though,

156
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:12,776
as each of these only get one or two new sets of sounds this update.

157
00:06:12,776 --> 00:06:14,495
Cats can have royal sounds,

158
00:06:15,205 --> 00:06:17,194
pigs can have mini or big sounds,

159
00:06:17,828 --> 00:06:19,545
chickens can have picky sounds,

160
00:06:20,645 --> 00:06:22,444
and cows can have moody sounds.

161
00:06:26,327 --> 00:06:29,320
Now the reason this is the lowest of the positive changes

162
00:06:29,320 --> 00:06:32,475
is because I just have such a hard time getting used to these.

163
00:06:32,475 --> 00:06:33,935
Texture changes I can handle,

164
00:06:33,935 --> 00:06:37,510
but for some reason I have a lot harder of a time accepting sound changes,

165
00:06:37,510 --> 00:06:38,825
like I'm still not very used to

166
00:06:38,825 --> 00:06:40,600
hearing the different wolf variants in the game.

167
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,260
Call me nostalgia blind all you want,

168
00:06:42,260 --> 00:06:43,442
but I have a feeling that I'll just

169
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:45,722
prefer the classic sounds for each of these animals.

170
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:46,374
Seven.

171
00:06:46,374 --> 00:06:47,660
New librarian trade.

172
00:06:47,658 --> 00:06:48,885
As I mentioned earlier,

173
00:06:48,885 --> 00:06:51,075
the librarian had to get a new master level trade

174
00:06:51,075 --> 00:06:53,105
to replace the previous nametag trade.

175
00:06:53,105 --> 00:06:55,135
Now, instead of getting a nametag,

176
00:06:55,140 --> 00:06:57,611
you'll unlock the groundbreaking trade of...

177
00:06:57,610 --> 00:06:59,120
a red and yellow candle.

178
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,200
Or as I like to call it,

179
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:01,697
the ketchup and mustard trade.

180
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:04,216
Okay, this is far from the most exciting trade,

181
00:07:04,216 --> 00:07:07,350
but I do see more value in it than the wandering trader nametag.

182
00:07:07,350 --> 00:07:10,160
It's kind of nice to have an easy way to get candles without bees,

183
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:13,058
but it's weird that it's only for the red and yellow candles.

184
00:07:13,060 --> 00:07:15,502
Maybe you'll be able to get other colors from different biomes

185
00:07:15,502 --> 00:07:18,150
when they finally remember about the villager rebalance update.

186
00:07:18,150 --> 00:07:20,190
I doubt I'm going to use this trade much at all,

187
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:23,451
but I do think it makes at least a little sense as a replacement trade.

188
00:07:23,450 --> 00:07:23,990
Six.

189
00:07:23,990 --> 00:07:25,520
Nametag crafting recipe.

190
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:27,600
Sorry again for spoiling you all earlier,

191
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:30,100
but yes, the nametag does have a crafting recipe now.

192
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:32,850
It takes one piece of paper and a nugget of any kind,

193
00:07:32,850 --> 00:07:34,245
making it extremely cheap.

194
00:07:34,245 --> 00:07:37,445
Honestly though, I don't really know if I like this addition.

195
00:07:37,445 --> 00:07:40,208
Nametags acted as a good reward for exploring structures

196
00:07:40,208 --> 00:07:41,535
and getting lucky while fishing.

197
00:07:41,535 --> 00:07:42,755
They weren't too rare,

198
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:44,558
but it made each structure that could be found in

199
00:07:44,558 --> 00:07:46,228
a bit more exciting to loot.

200
00:07:46,228 --> 00:07:48,320
If you did desperately need nametags,

201
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:51,139
then you could always trade with the librarian to get as many as you need

202
00:07:51,139 --> 00:07:53,195
at the cost of a pretty good chunk of emeralds.

203
00:07:53,195 --> 00:07:55,585
I personally feel like that was pretty well balanced,

204
00:07:55,590 --> 00:07:59,192
especially since most players never really need that many nametags.

205
00:07:59,192 --> 00:08:02,292
Maybe if you're working on a project where you need to name a ton of mobs

206
00:08:02,290 --> 00:08:03,625
to keep them from despawning,

207
00:08:03,630 --> 00:08:05,529
but I feel like if you're doing something like that,

208
00:08:05,530 --> 00:08:07,843
you probably have the skill to just get a villager.

209
00:08:07,843 --> 00:08:10,430
I'm not going to say this addition is necessarily bad,

210
00:08:10,430 --> 00:08:12,420
I mean it did crack the top half of the list,

211
00:08:12,420 --> 00:08:13,975
I just don't think it was needed

212
00:08:13,975 --> 00:08:16,865
and makes structures a little bit less exciting to explore.

213
00:08:16,870 --> 00:08:17,537
Five.

214
00:08:17,537 --> 00:08:18,655
New rabbit model.

215
00:08:18,655 --> 00:08:20,435
On top of getting new baby versions,

216
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:23,586
the adult rabbits were also completely overhauled here.

217
00:08:23,590 --> 00:08:26,003
They are not beating their reddit chungus allegations.

218
00:08:26,003 --> 00:08:29,105
Personally, I never had an issue with the original rabbit model,

219
00:08:29,105 --> 00:08:31,080
but a lot of others seem to think it sucked,

220
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:32,608
so I'm happy for them, I guess.

221
00:08:32,610 --> 00:08:34,862
For me, these feel maybe a little too fat,

222
00:08:34,862 --> 00:08:36,580
but whatever, I don't really care.

223
00:08:36,580 --> 00:08:38,480
It's nice they have new animations too,

224
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:40,076
I mean look how cute this one is.

225
00:08:41,765 --> 00:08:43,510
Four, the new baby mobs.

226
00:08:43,505 --> 00:08:46,192
Alright, we have finally rejoined with all of the people

227
00:08:46,190 --> 00:08:48,092
that used the baby chapter earlier.

228
00:08:48,731 --> 00:08:51,557
Those dweebs don't even know about the polar bear change.

229
00:08:52,925 --> 00:08:54,408
But yes, this is where I'm going to be

230
00:08:54,408 --> 00:08:56,741
grouping all of the baby mob retextures together,

231
00:08:56,741 --> 00:08:57,953
but with so many babies,

232
00:08:57,950 --> 00:08:59,603
some are bound to be worse than others.

233
00:08:59,603 --> 00:09:02,975
So now it's finally time to rank every baby mob retexture

234
00:09:02,975 --> 00:09:04,657
from the worst to the best.

235
00:09:04,660 --> 00:09:07,542
I'm simply judging these based on how cute I think each of them are.

236
00:09:07,540 --> 00:09:09,904
Sorry if your favorite place is low down on the list,

237
00:09:09,904 --> 00:09:11,275
you should just get better taste.

238
00:09:11,275 --> 00:09:13,225
We'll be running through these pretty quick because we have

239
00:09:13,225 --> 00:09:15,125
71 babies to look at.

240
00:09:15,130 --> 00:09:16,491
There are technically more,

241
00:09:16,491 --> 00:09:20,019
but I decided to combine the horse, llama, and axolotl variants together

242
00:09:20,019 --> 00:09:21,850
since my thoughts are the same for each of them.

243
00:09:21,850 --> 00:09:22,920
But no more delaying,

244
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:24,310
let's get into this list.

245
00:09:24,310 --> 00:09:27,360
71, the zombie villager, and 70, the villager.

246
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:30,935
These two babies are absolutely horrendous in my opinion.

247
00:09:30,935 --> 00:09:32,342
It looks like all they did

248
00:09:32,342 --> 00:09:35,391
was just delete the two bottom rows of pixels from the baby's head

249
00:09:35,391 --> 00:09:36,420
and called it a day.

250
00:09:36,420 --> 00:09:38,442
The reason I'm putting the zombie villager in last

251
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:40,536
is because it can visibly wear armor.

252
00:09:40,536 --> 00:09:42,065
To go with the baby mob changes,

253
00:09:42,065 --> 00:09:44,240
they also made new textures for baby armor,

254
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:47,149
and I honestly don't like how they look at all.

255
00:09:47,149 --> 00:09:48,570
Some pieces are okay,

256
00:09:48,570 --> 00:09:51,270
but the boots in particular are really bad.

257
00:09:51,270 --> 00:09:52,958
What are the-

258
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:57,244
What's even more embarrassing is that they originally looked even worse.

259
00:09:57,790 --> 00:09:59,658
Luckily the backlash was so great

260
00:09:59,658 --> 00:10:01,352
that they went back and fixed these a bit.

261
00:10:01,352 --> 00:10:04,475
But I still think I prefer the original look from before this drop.

262
00:10:04,475 --> 00:10:08,385
That's especially because baby armor does not display armor trims now,

263
00:10:08,390 --> 00:10:10,480
which was not the case in previous updates.

264
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:12,175
That's just a straight downgrade,

265
00:10:12,180 --> 00:10:12,792
and I can't believe

266
00:10:12,792 --> 00:10:15,533
they didn't at least try to make some armor trim textures.

267
00:10:15,533 --> 00:10:18,225
But whatever, these two are easily my least favorite babies

268
00:10:18,225 --> 00:10:20,310
and are far worse than what we had originally.

269
00:10:20,310 --> 00:10:23,930
69, the zombie, 68, the husk, and 67, the gurgle.

270
00:10:23,930 --> 00:10:26,515
I'm sorry, I hate how all of their faces look.

271
00:10:26,515 --> 00:10:28,392
They have a similar problem as the villagers

272
00:10:28,392 --> 00:10:30,875
where it just looks like they shaved pixels off of their head.

273
00:10:30,875 --> 00:10:33,305
I hate how the eyes and mouth touch the edges.

274
00:10:33,305 --> 00:10:35,805
The retexture just looks extremely sloppy.

275
00:10:35,805 --> 00:10:38,742
That's really bad here because I feel like the baby zombie

276
00:10:38,742 --> 00:10:41,355
is probably the most iconic baby in the game.

277
00:10:41,355 --> 00:10:42,800
You know, chicken jockey and all that.

278
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:45,008
I really would have thought that they'd put more effort into

279
00:10:45,008 --> 00:10:46,926
at least making this guy look good,

280
00:10:46,926 --> 00:10:49,600
but no, it's definitely worse than the original now.

281
00:10:49,595 --> 00:10:51,290
Add on the worse armor as well,

282
00:10:51,290 --> 00:10:52,592
and it's clear that Mojang just

283
00:10:52,592 --> 00:10:55,414
didn't do a fantastic job on the humanoid babies.

284
00:10:55,414 --> 00:10:57,708
Of this group, I like the baby drown the best

285
00:10:57,708 --> 00:11:00,245
just because it got a unique name being the gurgle.

286
00:11:00,250 --> 00:11:01,342
That is kind of funny.

287
00:11:01,892 --> 00:11:02,800
Ben gurgled.

288
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:04,330
66, the strider.

289
00:11:04,330 --> 00:11:06,760
This thing is just absurdly ugly.

290
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:08,573
Look at the top of his head.

291
00:11:09,110 --> 00:11:11,680
I just can't find anything to like about this model.

292
00:11:11,680 --> 00:11:12,970
It just looks gross.

293
00:11:12,970 --> 00:11:14,385
65, the sheep.

294
00:11:14,385 --> 00:11:17,730
It really feels like there was not much effort put into this design at all.

295
00:11:17,730 --> 00:11:19,392
Compared to the other main farm animals

296
00:11:19,392 --> 00:11:21,430
that have really cute baby redesigns,

297
00:11:21,430 --> 00:11:24,054
the sheep is left with this weird ugly mess.

298
00:11:24,050 --> 00:11:28,610
He's got a horrible hairline and his entire design just feels too simplistic.

299
00:11:28,610 --> 00:11:30,375
It doesn't even feel like this baby design

300
00:11:30,375 --> 00:11:32,643
should grow up into what we have for the sheep.

301
00:11:32,643 --> 00:11:33,725
Also, can we just talk about

302
00:11:33,725 --> 00:11:36,450
how the Mojang devs seem to hate the sheep for some reason?

303
00:11:36,450 --> 00:11:38,415
It's one of the core four farm animals,

304
00:11:38,415 --> 00:11:41,100
but it's treated like absolute garbage in comparison.

305
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:43,095
It got no buy-in variants,

306
00:11:43,095 --> 00:11:44,540
no new sound effects,

307
00:11:44,540 --> 00:11:46,565
and the worst looking baby by far.

308
00:11:46,570 --> 00:11:50,052
What could the sheep have possibly done to deserve this treatment?

309
00:11:50,938 --> 00:11:52,540
Because sheep killed my grandma, okay?

310
00:11:52,535 --> 00:11:55,605
64, zombified piglin and 63, piglin.

311
00:11:55,610 --> 00:11:58,554
These two are definitely a lot cuter than what we saw with the zombies,

312
00:11:58,554 --> 00:12:00,510
but there are still a few weird things about them.

313
00:12:00,510 --> 00:12:02,895
Of course, I already talked about how bad the armor is,

314
00:12:02,895 --> 00:12:04,265
but for the zombified piglin,

315
00:12:04,265 --> 00:12:07,210
I just don't like how his nose overlaps with his eyehole.

316
00:12:07,210 --> 00:12:09,515
That's not the case for the adult zombified piglins,

317
00:12:09,515 --> 00:12:11,535
so it kind of comes off as a mistake here.

318
00:12:11,540 --> 00:12:14,546
Items in these babies' hands also clip into their heads sometimes,

319
00:12:14,546 --> 00:12:15,990
which isn't the worst thing ever,

320
00:12:15,990 --> 00:12:17,399
but it does look a bit weird.

321
00:12:17,399 --> 00:12:18,800
62, hoglin.

322
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:22,179
His eyes are way too massive and his head is a bit wide,

323
00:12:22,180 --> 00:12:24,116
but other than that, this is just okay.

324
00:12:24,116 --> 00:12:25,750
61, cold cow.

325
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:28,705
I'm putting this one much lower than the other cow variants because,

326
00:12:28,705 --> 00:12:29,945
correct me if I'm wrong,

327
00:12:29,945 --> 00:12:32,550
but the horns here are just not correct on this guy.

328
00:12:32,550 --> 00:12:35,071
The cold cow's horns normally point straight ahead,

329
00:12:35,071 --> 00:12:37,750
so it's weird that the baby model has them pointing upward.

330
00:12:37,750 --> 00:12:39,955
Maybe when this type of cow is a baby in real life,

331
00:12:39,955 --> 00:12:41,420
their horns are like this,

332
00:12:41,420 --> 00:12:43,366
but to me, it just seems odd.

333
00:12:43,366 --> 00:12:44,900
60, the killer bunny.

334
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:46,800
Look at the five head on this thing.

335
00:12:48,365 --> 00:12:50,454
Since the killer bunny's eyes are horizontal

336
00:12:50,454 --> 00:12:52,330
instead of vertical like the other rabbits,

337
00:12:52,330 --> 00:12:55,395
his face does not fit on the baby model nearly as well.

338
00:12:55,395 --> 00:12:58,070
Maybe it's the point that he's supposed to be a little ugly,

339
00:12:58,070 --> 00:12:59,830
but this might be a bit too much.

340
00:12:59,830 --> 00:13:03,958
59, the mule, 58, the skeleton horse, 57, the donkey,

341
00:13:03,958 --> 00:13:06,845
56, the horse, and 55, the zombie horse.

342
00:13:06,850 --> 00:13:09,518
I'm keeping all of these together for a couple reasons.

343
00:13:09,520 --> 00:13:12,540
Obviously, for starters, they're all some kind of horse-like model.

344
00:13:13,330 --> 00:13:15,492
I'm not separating all of the different horse colors

345
00:13:15,492 --> 00:13:18,890
because there's like a million of them and feel the exact same for each one.

346
00:13:18,890 --> 00:13:21,275
The issue with this group of babies is that I feel like

347
00:13:21,275 --> 00:13:23,585
the head is just a bit too wide and blocky.

348
00:13:23,585 --> 00:13:26,185
Like, there's some actual shape to an adult horse's head,

349
00:13:26,185 --> 00:13:29,550
but the babies just get a rectangle which doesn't look very good.

350
00:13:29,550 --> 00:13:30,810
As for their order here,

351
00:13:30,810 --> 00:13:32,442
I like the mule and donkey the least

352
00:13:32,442 --> 00:13:34,665
because their eye just being a single black pixel

353
00:13:34,665 --> 00:13:37,440
doesn't look as good as the horse which has white in his eyes.

354
00:13:37,435 --> 00:13:38,855
Also, as an additional note,

355
00:13:38,860 --> 00:13:41,240
you can't get the skeleton and zombie horses in survival,

356
00:13:41,240 --> 00:13:44,235
but they got a retexture here so I feel like it made sense to include them.

357
00:13:44,235 --> 00:13:47,175
Hey, wait a minute, why'd Mojang do them and not the camel husk?

358
00:13:47,175 --> 00:13:48,840
Free him, he doesn't deserve this!

359
00:13:48,840 --> 00:13:50,350
54, the llamas.

360
00:13:50,350 --> 00:13:52,858
Like the horse, I'm including all the colors together here

361
00:13:52,858 --> 00:13:54,175
along with the trader version.

362
00:13:54,175 --> 00:13:56,270
I've heard a lot of people say these guys look weird,

363
00:13:56,270 --> 00:13:57,365
and while I do agree,

364
00:13:57,365 --> 00:13:59,040
I also just kind of find them funny.

365
00:13:59,040 --> 00:14:01,092
The lack of eyebrows compared to the adult version

366
00:14:01,092 --> 00:14:03,065
make these guys have a pretty funny stare.

367
00:14:03,070 --> 00:14:05,678
53 - 47, most of the cats.

368
00:14:05,680 --> 00:14:06,966
From this point on in the list,

369
00:14:06,966 --> 00:14:10,350
we've got the babies that I think are improvements over what we had before.

370
00:14:10,350 --> 00:14:11,408
It's a bit of a shame

371
00:14:11,408 --> 00:14:13,970
that about a third of the babies are downgrades in my eyes,

372
00:14:13,970 --> 00:14:15,820
but at least they got most of them correct.

373
00:14:15,820 --> 00:14:17,769
The kittens are all extremely cute.

374
00:14:17,769 --> 00:14:18,758
I think in a vacuum,

375
00:14:18,758 --> 00:14:21,640
their proportions are pretty perfect for making them look very cuddly.

376
00:14:21,640 --> 00:14:25,215
However, issues arise when you also look at the adult cats.

377
00:14:25,529 --> 00:14:28,056
Why do the babies have bigger heads than the adults?

378
00:14:28,056 --> 00:14:31,015
Like, do the adults just get stupider when they grow up or something?

379
00:14:31,015 --> 00:14:32,480
This isn't a huge deal,

380
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:35,050
but it makes the kittens feel a lot bigger than they should be.

381
00:14:35,050 --> 00:14:36,092
Now, the reason I decided to

382
00:14:36,092 --> 00:14:38,936
split up some of the cats and not them all under one number

383
00:14:38,936 --> 00:14:40,992
is because I do think certain cat breeds

384
00:14:40,992 --> 00:14:43,265
look a lot better with the baby model than others.

385
00:14:43,265 --> 00:14:45,325
The Persian cat is definitely my least favorite

386
00:14:45,325 --> 00:14:46,665
since it doesn't have a snout.

387
00:14:46,670 --> 00:14:49,131
It kinda just makes it look like it has a pancake face.

388
00:14:49,131 --> 00:14:50,855
The other breeds that I put down here,

389
00:14:50,855 --> 00:14:56,045
in order, are Siamese, White, Tuxedo, Black, Calico, and Tabby.

390
00:14:56,045 --> 00:14:59,408
All of these I don't love as much just because I think the one-pixel eyes

391
00:14:59,408 --> 00:15:00,525
look a bit weird on them.

392
00:15:00,530 --> 00:15:03,025
Luckily, there are four more cat breeds that I like better

393
00:15:03,025 --> 00:15:04,323
that we'll be seeing in a bit,

394
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:07,080
but these are all held back because of their haunting stares.

395
00:15:09,051 --> 00:15:10,650
46, the Dolphin.

396
00:15:10,650 --> 00:15:11,910
The model looks pretty good,

397
00:15:11,910 --> 00:15:14,825
but this is another case of a baby mob having a one-pixel eye

398
00:15:14,825 --> 00:15:16,045
that I don't really love.

399
00:15:16,045 --> 00:15:18,860
45, the armadillo, and 44, the polar bear.

400
00:15:18,860 --> 00:15:21,305
Honestly, if you told me these two were unchanged,

401
00:15:21,305 --> 00:15:22,675
I'd completely believe you.

402
00:15:22,675 --> 00:15:25,345
When you look at them side-by-side with their original versions,

403
00:15:25,350 --> 00:15:26,801
it does become obvious,

404
00:15:26,801 --> 00:15:29,210
but these are not mobs I interact with very much.

405
00:15:29,210 --> 00:15:31,098
43, the Axolotls.

406
00:15:31,098 --> 00:15:33,670
I like that their heads are now noticeably bigger than their torso.

407
00:15:33,670 --> 00:15:36,895
It makes them look a lot cuter and more in line with other baby mobs.

408
00:15:36,900 --> 00:15:39,350
42, the aquid, and 41, the glow squid.

409
00:15:39,350 --> 00:15:43,020
Honestly, I keep forgetting they even added the baby squids to Java Edition

410
00:15:43,020 --> 00:15:44,565
in the Bundles of Bravery drop.

411
00:15:44,565 --> 00:15:46,095
We still can't breed squids,

412
00:15:46,095 --> 00:15:47,200
which is unfortunate,

413
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:50,195
but at least on the rare occasions we do see the babies in the wild,

414
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:51,389
they are pretty cute.

415
00:15:51,390 --> 00:15:54,275
I like how stubby these two are compared to their adult versions.

416
00:15:54,280 --> 00:15:56,241
They definitely give off plushy vibes.

417
00:15:56,241 --> 00:15:57,955
I mean, that is kind of this whole update.

418
00:15:57,960 --> 00:16:00,930
I'm sure they're gonna sell a ton of baby merchandise in the future,

419
00:16:00,930 --> 00:16:03,200
but these two are especially plush-feeling.

420
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:05,805
40-34, the rabbits.

421
00:16:05,805 --> 00:16:07,358
Except you!

422
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:09,391
Unlike the Killer Bunny we saw before,

423
00:16:09,391 --> 00:16:12,510
these rabbits have vertical eyes which match their heads much better.

424
00:16:12,510 --> 00:16:16,462
Honestly, I prefer the baby look a lot more to their adult versions.

425
00:16:16,462 --> 00:16:19,742
Their proportions look better to me than the gigantic rectangle bodies

426
00:16:19,742 --> 00:16:21,192
seen on the adult rabbits.

427
00:16:21,192 --> 00:16:23,680
Their order here is just based on which color I like best,

428
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:29,211
so it goes black, toast, white, white splotched, gold, brown, and salt.

429
00:16:29,211 --> 00:16:30,630
33, the zoglin.

430
00:16:30,630 --> 00:16:32,630
Okay, I don't know exactly what it is,

431
00:16:32,630 --> 00:16:35,042
but the eyes on this guy just look so much better to me

432
00:16:35,042 --> 00:16:36,720
than they did with the regular Hoglin.

433
00:16:36,720 --> 00:16:39,160
Maybe it's because half of his face has been melted off,

434
00:16:39,160 --> 00:16:42,415
but whatever it is, I do like the zoglin much more than the hoglin.

435
00:16:42,415 --> 00:16:43,920
32, the goat.

436
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:46,251
What's Mario doing on this list?

437
00:16:46,881 --> 00:16:49,580
This guy just looks really cute, not much else to say on that.

438
00:16:49,580 --> 00:16:51,055
31, the snifflet.

439
00:16:51,055 --> 00:16:54,460
This guy does come close to having a head that's a little bit too wide,

440
00:16:54,460 --> 00:16:55,880
but I think it works on the sniffer

441
00:16:55,880 --> 00:16:58,585
because his massive nose is the whole focus of the mob.

442
00:16:58,585 --> 00:17:00,225
30, the panda.

443
00:17:00,225 --> 00:17:01,192
Guys,

444
00:17:01,190 --> 00:17:04,165
I think the Panda got possessed by Herobrine.

445
00:17:04,658 --> 00:17:05,540
Oh no, wait, we're good.

446
00:17:05,540 --> 00:17:07,445
The white eyes are maybe a little weird,

447
00:17:07,445 --> 00:17:09,085
but I honestly kind of like them too.

448
00:17:09,085 --> 00:17:11,820
It's also nice to get variants for all the different panda types.

449
00:17:11,820 --> 00:17:13,525
My favorite is probably the playful one

450
00:17:13,525 --> 00:17:15,210
just for being full of joy and whimsy.

451
00:17:15,210 --> 00:17:16,540
29, the turtle.

452
00:17:16,540 --> 00:17:17,642
These are very cute,

453
00:17:17,642 --> 00:17:20,618
I love how much they're able to detail here with so little pixels.

454
00:17:20,618 --> 00:17:24,030
The only negative that I have is that they feel a bit too big.

455
00:17:24,030 --> 00:17:26,380
The original baby turtles were minuscule,

456
00:17:26,380 --> 00:17:28,235
and I think that was a big part of their charm.

457
00:17:28,235 --> 00:17:29,825
They are still pretty small now,

458
00:17:29,825 --> 00:17:31,358
but I think the mob would've been cuter

459
00:17:31,358 --> 00:17:33,440
if they shrunk it down just a little bit further.

460
00:17:33,440 --> 00:17:34,605
28, the bee.

461
00:17:34,605 --> 00:17:38,065
This is another case where I think I prefer the baby mob over the adult,

462
00:17:38,065 --> 00:17:40,295
the size just fits with being a bee a lot better.

463
00:17:40,295 --> 00:17:43,342
It's also very funny when a baby bee interacts with a flower

464
00:17:43,342 --> 00:17:45,760
because it gets absolutely covered in pollen.

465
00:17:45,760 --> 00:17:48,115
27 - 25, the pigs.

466
00:17:48,115 --> 00:17:51,358
We finally got our second member of the core four farm animals

467
00:17:51,360 --> 00:17:53,488
after seeing the sheep quite a while ago.

468
00:17:53,953 --> 00:17:56,519
Cold cows aren't real.

469
00:17:56,519 --> 00:17:59,562
They did a really good job chipifying this mob's design.

470
00:17:59,562 --> 00:18:00,930
I'm not exactly sure why,

471
00:18:00,925 --> 00:18:03,892
but I think the singular pixel eyes also work better on the pig

472
00:18:03,892 --> 00:18:06,058
compared to some of the other mobs we've already seen.

473
00:18:06,060 --> 00:18:09,521
As for their order, I just put them in based on which pig biome I like best,

474
00:18:09,520 --> 00:18:12,005
so it goes cold, warm, then classic.

475
00:18:12,005 --> 00:18:13,708
24, the camel.

476
00:18:13,708 --> 00:18:15,158
They took his hump!

477
00:18:15,158 --> 00:18:17,088
I'm assuming that's how camels are in real life,

478
00:18:17,088 --> 00:18:18,258
and I think that was a good change

479
00:18:18,258 --> 00:18:20,820
to make the baby stand out even more from the adults.

480
00:18:20,815 --> 00:18:24,975
But the question is, are baby camels better than adult camels

481
00:18:24,980 --> 00:18:26,567
in camel drop?

482
00:18:29,840 --> 00:18:31,365
No, they aren't.

483
00:18:31,365 --> 00:18:34,485
23 - 20, all of the cows and mooshrooms.

484
00:18:34,485 --> 00:18:35,945
Stop bringing up the cold cow,

485
00:18:35,945 --> 00:18:36,715
who even is that?

486
00:18:36,715 --> 00:18:38,635
Since these two mobs are just color swaps,

487
00:18:38,635 --> 00:18:40,375
I think it makes sense for them to be together.

488
00:18:40,375 --> 00:18:42,540
They did a great job shrinking down the cow,

489
00:18:42,540 --> 00:18:45,270
while also making it beefier than something like the baby pig.

490
00:18:45,270 --> 00:18:46,483
Their models are all the same,

491
00:18:46,483 --> 00:18:48,695
so their order is based on which color I like best,

492
00:18:48,695 --> 00:18:52,920
which goes brown mooshroom, warm cow, classic cow, and the red mooshroom.

493
00:18:52,920 --> 00:18:55,360
19-16, the rest of the cats.

494
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:58,495
We still have four more cats to talk about that we didn't mention earlier.

495
00:18:58,495 --> 00:19:01,300
That's because this set doesn't have such creepy eyes,

496
00:19:01,300 --> 00:19:03,354
so I find them to be significantly cuter.

497
00:19:03,354 --> 00:19:04,480
First is the jelly cat,

498
00:19:04,480 --> 00:19:07,299
which I think is helped by the gray pixels next to its eyes.

499
00:19:07,299 --> 00:19:08,700
They aren't part of the eyes,

500
00:19:08,700 --> 00:19:10,080
but it sort of looks that way,

501
00:19:10,080 --> 00:19:12,192
and helps make this baby look a lot cuter to me.

502
00:19:12,192 --> 00:19:14,675
Next is the red cat, and it looks like there are absolutely

503
00:19:14,675 --> 00:19:16,410
zero thoughts going on in its head.

504
00:19:16,410 --> 00:19:19,693
And then my two favorite cats are the Ragdoll and the British Shorthair,

505
00:19:19,693 --> 00:19:21,870
because they have dark blue and black eyes respectively,

506
00:19:21,870 --> 00:19:23,292
which look so much more natural than

507
00:19:23,292 --> 00:19:25,325
than the colored eyes of the other baby cats.

508
00:19:25,325 --> 00:19:27,471
These seem like the least likely to stare into my soul,

509
00:19:27,471 --> 00:19:29,092
so I like them more than the rest.

510
00:19:29,092 --> 00:19:30,380
15, the ocelot.

511
00:19:30,380 --> 00:19:33,775
The mob itself may be useless, but it's got a pretty cute baby.

512
00:19:33,775 --> 00:19:34,965
As far as I can tell,

513
00:19:34,970 --> 00:19:37,264
it uses the same model as the rest of the kittens,

514
00:19:37,260 --> 00:19:40,099
but what makes me like it the most are once again its eyes.

515
00:19:40,099 --> 00:19:43,330
The darker pixels at the top help make the eyes look a lot less empty,

516
00:19:43,330 --> 00:19:46,595
and in my opinion makes the ocelot the cutest cat-like mob.

517
00:19:46,595 --> 00:19:49,235
14, the fox, and 13, the snowy fox.

518
00:19:49,235 --> 00:19:51,800
These two just look so incredibly cuddly.

519
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:53,613
Their proportions are absolutely perfect,

520
00:19:53,610 --> 00:19:55,358
and I would love to have one as a pet.

521
00:19:55,358 --> 00:19:56,590
To be totally honest,

522
00:19:56,590 --> 00:19:59,825
these babies kind of ruin my perception of the normal fox.

523
00:19:59,830 --> 00:20:01,890
The adult's eyes look so weird,

524
00:20:01,890 --> 00:20:05,213
and honestly kind of creepy being at the edge of their head like that.

525
00:20:06,224 --> 00:20:09,400
I think foxes benefited a ton from this update.

526
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:12,134
12 - 4, all of the wolf variants.

527
00:20:12,130 --> 00:20:13,447
Dogs are my favorite animal,

528
00:20:13,450 --> 00:20:16,647
so of course I was going to absolutely love the puppies.

529
00:20:17,149 --> 00:20:20,985
All along, I was the heckin' doggo redditor.

530
00:20:20,990 --> 00:20:23,213
This update is my fault.

531
00:20:23,213 --> 00:20:25,158
In all seriousness, these pups look

532
00:20:25,158 --> 00:20:27,859
so much better than the original wolf babies.

533
00:20:27,859 --> 00:20:30,375
I think these might be the mobs that benefited the most

534
00:20:30,375 --> 00:20:33,278
from the one-pixel eyes that most of the babies seem to receive.

535
00:20:33,278 --> 00:20:36,320
That's not to mention how much better their proportions are here too.

536
00:20:36,315 --> 00:20:37,775
Just scrolling down the wiki page

537
00:20:37,775 --> 00:20:40,225
made me really sad that I can't pet any of these guys.

538
00:20:40,230 --> 00:20:41,722
They're all super adorable.

539
00:20:42,242 --> 00:20:46,020
As for their order, I put them in based on which biome variant I like best.

540
00:20:46,015 --> 00:20:47,570
So going from worst to best,

541
00:20:47,570 --> 00:20:51,485
we have spotted, stripped, snowy, black, chestnut,

542
00:20:51,490 --> 00:20:54,323
rusty, ashen, woods, and classic.

543
00:20:54,320 --> 00:20:56,050
Out of all the babies in this video,

544
00:20:56,050 --> 00:20:58,385
this is probably the set I'm most excited to see.

545
00:20:58,385 --> 00:21:00,575
But I couldn't quite give them the number one spot

546
00:21:00,575 --> 00:21:02,965
because we also have to look at the three chickens.

547
00:21:02,970 --> 00:21:06,300
Mojang has plastered these chicks all over the marketing for this update

548
00:21:06,300 --> 00:21:07,530
and it's clear to see why.

549
00:21:07,530 --> 00:21:10,200
They're by far the most changed from their original design,

550
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:11,925
now taking on the form of tiny cubes

551
00:21:11,925 --> 00:21:13,863
instead of just being smaller chickens.

552
00:21:13,863 --> 00:21:17,455
That makes them both look so much funnier and also more accurate as well.

553
00:21:17,455 --> 00:21:20,590
So I think the chickens 100% deserve the top spots.

554
00:21:20,590 --> 00:21:21,892
Cold is my least favorite

555
00:21:21,892 --> 00:21:22,875
just because I kinda like

556
00:21:22,875 --> 00:21:24,995
how the warm chicken looks like it's been cooked a little.

557
00:21:24,995 --> 00:21:27,600
Of course, the classic chicken has to be the best due to

558
00:21:27,600 --> 00:21:30,980
going as far as to change its color scheme to yellow when in chick form.

559
00:21:30,980 --> 00:21:33,655
So for having the biggest and best model change,

560
00:21:33,660 --> 00:21:37,486
the classic chick takes the crown as the best baby mob in Minecraft.

561
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:39,575
But anyways,

562
00:21:39,575 --> 00:21:40,520
that's not it for the video,

563
00:21:40,515 --> 00:21:41,165
don't click off!

564
00:21:41,165 --> 00:21:43,392
Remember, we still have three more features to rank

565
00:21:43,392 --> 00:21:45,656
that I feel belong above the babies.

566
00:21:45,656 --> 00:21:47,460
So to get back into the normal list here,

567
00:21:47,460 --> 00:21:49,658
we have three, the golden dandelion.

568
00:21:49,660 --> 00:21:51,281
If you look at the wiki page,

569
00:21:51,281 --> 00:21:54,725
this is the one lone addition that is said to be added for this drop.

570
00:21:54,730 --> 00:21:56,325
I find that very funny.

571
00:21:56,325 --> 00:21:57,308
These can be obtained by

572
00:21:57,308 --> 00:22:00,376
surrounding a dandelion with eight gold nuggets and a crafting table.

573
00:22:00,376 --> 00:22:02,558
On top of just being a flower you can place down to

574
00:22:02,558 --> 00:22:04,492
flex your wealth of a single gold ingot,

575
00:22:04,492 --> 00:22:06,895
this does have a use relating to the baby mobs.

576
00:22:06,895 --> 00:22:09,492
You can feed a golden dandelion to almost any baby

577
00:22:09,492 --> 00:22:11,265
and it'll keep them as a baby forever.

578
00:22:11,265 --> 00:22:14,715
That was a very important addition because if they didn't add this,

579
00:22:14,715 --> 00:22:18,042
it would make remodeling all of the babies even more useless

580
00:22:18,040 --> 00:22:21,045
since they would only exist like that for 20 minutes each.

581
00:22:21,045 --> 00:22:24,160
If you do end up changing your mind and want your animal to be old again,

582
00:22:24,160 --> 00:22:26,325
then you can always give them another golden dandelion

583
00:22:26,325 --> 00:22:27,455
to undo the effect.

584
00:22:27,455 --> 00:22:29,975
While I am very happy this is here to make the update

585
00:22:29,975 --> 00:22:31,523
feel a bit more justified,

586
00:22:31,523 --> 00:22:33,920
I really don't see myself using this much at all.

587
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:35,740
I might keep a couple puppies,

588
00:22:35,740 --> 00:22:38,423
but besides that, I'm not touching this feature much.

589
00:22:38,423 --> 00:22:40,810
I'll probably use it mostly as a decoration tool,

590
00:22:40,810 --> 00:22:42,821
but even then, not very often.

591
00:22:42,821 --> 00:22:45,842
I also just have to say that the golden dandelion's implementation

592
00:22:45,842 --> 00:22:47,976
feels like a huge missed opportunity.

593
00:22:47,976 --> 00:22:50,501
First off, of all the flowers to make gold,

594
00:22:50,500 --> 00:22:52,925
they really chose the one that was already yellow.

595
00:22:52,925 --> 00:22:55,158
A gold poppy or cornflower or something

596
00:22:55,158 --> 00:22:57,450
would have been a far cooler decoration block.

597
00:22:57,450 --> 00:23:01,592
Secondly, the way you get the golden dandelion just feels very lame.

598
00:23:01,592 --> 00:23:03,506
Seeing as this is a flower,

599
00:23:03,506 --> 00:23:05,392
I think this could have been the perfect chance to

600
00:23:05,392 --> 00:23:07,808
finally give the sniffer a better use.

601
00:23:07,808 --> 00:23:10,725
Everyone complains about how pointless the sniffer feels

602
00:23:10,725 --> 00:23:14,525
because all it does is give the player two extremely niche flowers.

603
00:23:14,525 --> 00:23:18,089
If the golden dandelion or something like it was added to the pool though,

604
00:23:18,089 --> 00:23:21,090
it would give players a legitimate reason to look for a sniffer.

605
00:23:21,085 --> 00:23:23,100
It wouldn't be the most helpful use,

606
00:23:23,100 --> 00:23:25,406
like I said, I doubt I'm going to use this very much,

607
00:23:25,410 --> 00:23:28,401
but it would be significantly better than what the mob has now.

608
00:23:28,400 --> 00:23:31,592
Alternatively, maybe they could have finally added the moobloom this update

609
00:23:31,590 --> 00:23:34,007
and have it give the player the golden dandelion somehow.

610
00:23:34,007 --> 00:23:36,692
We know Mojang is willing to change a mob vote loser's use

611
00:23:36,692 --> 00:23:37,935
based on the copper golem.

612
00:23:37,935 --> 00:23:40,470
Seeing as so many people want the moobloom in the game,

613
00:23:40,470 --> 00:23:42,092
I think this would have been perfect.

614
00:23:42,092 --> 00:23:44,042
As it is now, the golden dandelion

615
00:23:44,042 --> 00:23:47,592
just has a simple crafting recipe using two fairly common materials,

616
00:23:47,592 --> 00:23:50,080
so it doesn't really open up for much unique gameplay.

617
00:23:50,080 --> 00:23:52,132
Overall, this is still a good addition,

618
00:23:52,130 --> 00:23:54,495
but I just wish they went about it in a different way.

619
00:23:54,495 --> 00:23:56,275
Two, stonecutter changes.

620
00:23:56,280 --> 00:23:59,402
In every other drop, this would be near the bottom of the ranking,

621
00:23:59,402 --> 00:24:01,425
but I think this is the first real feature here

622
00:24:01,425 --> 00:24:03,155
that I'm going to get a ton of use out of.

623
00:24:03,155 --> 00:24:05,630
If you're an avid user of a silk touch pickaxe,

624
00:24:05,630 --> 00:24:06,958
you likely know the annoyance of

625
00:24:06,960 --> 00:24:08,960
accidentally collecting a ton of deepslate

626
00:24:08,960 --> 00:24:11,045
when you really need cobbled deepslate.

627
00:24:11,045 --> 00:24:14,075
Previously, only cobbled deepslate could be used to craft

628
00:24:14,075 --> 00:24:15,925
any of the deepslate block variants,

629
00:24:15,925 --> 00:24:19,008
whereas the normal deep slop was literally useless.

630
00:24:19,008 --> 00:24:20,920
So if you had a large collection of it,

631
00:24:20,920 --> 00:24:22,975
you'd have to re-mine them with a normal pickaxe

632
00:24:22,975 --> 00:24:24,405
just to get the cobbled version.

633
00:24:24,405 --> 00:24:27,192
Luckily, Mojang finally realized how annoying that is

634
00:24:27,192 --> 00:24:29,825
and now lets you use the stonecutter to turn normal deepslate

635
00:24:29,825 --> 00:24:32,138
directly into any of the deepslate variants.

636
00:24:32,138 --> 00:24:34,492
This is such a good quality of life improvement

637
00:24:34,492 --> 00:24:36,636
and even extends outside of deepslate.

638
00:24:36,636 --> 00:24:38,425
Stoneblocks can now also be turned into

639
00:24:38,425 --> 00:24:40,425
any cobblestone block in the stonecutter.

640
00:24:40,425 --> 00:24:42,825
Overall, I'm very happy with this change that will

641
00:24:42,825 --> 00:24:45,293
make deepslate mining a lot less annoying.

642
00:24:45,290 --> 00:24:49,092
But with how absolutely phenomenal this update has been,

643
00:24:49,090 --> 00:24:51,851
what could possibly take the number one spot?

644
00:25:03,030 --> 00:25:05,681
I can't think of a more fitting winner for this drop

645
00:25:06,142 --> 00:25:07,590
than a fart sound effect.

646
00:25:07,590 --> 00:25:09,542
Noteblocks are given brand new trumpet sounds

647
00:25:09,542 --> 00:25:11,295
when placed on top of copper blocks.

648
00:25:11,295 --> 00:25:14,692
Having a new instrument is always going to be insanely useful

649
00:25:14,692 --> 00:25:16,208
for noteblock music makers,

650
00:25:16,208 --> 00:25:18,320
but these go even further than normal.

651
00:25:18,315 --> 00:25:20,985
There are actually four different types of trumpet sounds,

652
00:25:20,990 --> 00:25:22,915
one for each level of oxidation.

653
00:25:25,960 --> 00:25:28,160
This was a really cool idea,

654
00:25:28,155 --> 00:25:29,605
and as I already pointed out,

655
00:25:29,605 --> 00:25:32,430
the oxidized one is basically a fart sound effect.

656
00:25:32,430 --> 00:25:35,607
Now unfortunately, I'm not very good at making music.

657
00:25:39,040 --> 00:25:42,538
But I am good at being evil and nefarious.

658
00:25:44,342 --> 00:25:48,030
I know that I'm going to be using this fart sound effect so much.

659
00:25:48,025 --> 00:25:49,942
You can now basically make a whoopee cushion

660
00:25:49,940 --> 00:25:51,672
and put it in your friend's bases.

661
00:25:53,221 --> 00:25:54,670
Hew, pranked!

662
00:25:56,650 --> 00:25:59,849
You can tie this to any redstone input or even just a skulk sensor

663
00:25:59,849 --> 00:26:01,270
to make it harder totrack.

664
00:26:01,270 --> 00:26:03,675
There are so many ways you can use this sound effect

665
00:26:03,675 --> 00:26:06,585
and I'm very much looking forward to pranking my friends with it.

666
00:26:06,585 --> 00:26:07,760
Wait, I don't have those.

667
00:26:09,292 --> 00:26:11,570
So out of all the features in this update,

668
00:26:11,570 --> 00:26:14,960
I think this is the one that will bring me the most joy to use.

669
00:26:14,960 --> 00:26:16,325
It may seem stupid,

670
00:26:16,330 --> 00:26:20,261
but I think the best feature in this incredibly lackluster drop

671
00:26:20,260 --> 00:26:22,513
is without a doubt, the fart note block.

672
00:26:23,108 --> 00:26:25,244
But anyways, that's it for this video.

673
00:26:25,244 --> 00:26:27,442
Do you love the new baby chainmail leggings

674
00:26:27,442 --> 00:26:29,400
and hate me for saying the baby armor sucks?

675
00:26:29,400 --> 00:26:30,745
Let me know in the comments.

676
00:26:30,750 --> 00:26:33,129
Sorry if I was off-hating for a lot of this video,

677
00:26:33,129 --> 00:26:34,575
but luckily I think the next drop

678
00:26:34,575 --> 00:26:36,860
is already looking a lot better than this one.

679
00:26:36,860 --> 00:26:38,979
We're getting our first full blocks in over a year,

680
00:26:38,979 --> 00:26:40,263
so that's pretty exciting.

681
00:26:40,260 --> 00:26:41,795
But I've got to get back to doing my homework,

682
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:44,035
so before I go, I've got to thank my members being

683
00:26:44,035 --> 00:27:31,695
(SPONSORS)

684
00:27:31,695 --> 00:27:33,485
But anyways, dry bones for Smash,

685
00:27:33,490 --> 00:27:34,960
and I'll see you guys next time.

